                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.003/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jardine</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 23, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Your 36, March 19, 5 p.m. You may address a written communication to the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs stating that on the <pb facs="0279" n="159"
                        xml:id="pg_159"/> clear understanding that this Government’s consent has
                    been requested by the Egyptian Government you have been authorized to consent to
                    the collection from American nationals of the excise tax on matches. At the same
                    time you should add that this Government will not be in a position to give
                    consideration to the possibility of withdrawing its reservations to the law and
                    decree of February 11 until it has had an opportunity to study the official
                    texts thereof and the circumstances under which they were promulgated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
